This project was developed as part of a course, focusing on the use of APIs. The main goal is to display relevant data attractively and functionally using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Various features, pedagogical modalities, detailed evaluation of elements, and information filtering have been implemented.

Features
API Consumption: Integrates the Dragon Ball API to fetch and display data such as images, descriptions, names, and/or characteristics.
Data Presentation: Information is organized and displayed in cards, tables, etc., for an intuitive user experience.
UI Respect: The user interface follows the design guidelines of the DB company to maintain visual coherence.
Documentation: The project is properly documented in this README to facilitate understanding and replication.
Pedagogical Modalities
Pedagogical modalities have been included to enhance the learning, exploration, and understanding of the project.

Evaluation Modalities
The project offers evaluation modalities that allow viewing the details of a single element, filtering information through a search bar, or categories.

Pedagogical Modalities:
Single Element Detail: Allows examining in detail the information of a single element from the API.
Information Filtering: Implements a filtering system that facilitates searching for specific data by categories or through a search bar.
Evaluation Modalities:
View Single Element Detail: Provides detailed information about a selected element.
Information Filtering: Allows users to filter information according to specific criteria for a more precise search.
